<P>A LETTER TO Mr. DAVID HUME, ON THE TRAGEDY OF DOUGLAS; Its ANALYSIS: AND THE CHARGE again&s;t Mr. GARRICK&punc; By an ENGLISH CRITIC.</P>
<Q>&mdash; &mdash; <HI>Sic ais, a&s;t ego contra.</HI></Q>
<Q>So thou faye&s;t; but I am of a contrary Opinion.</Q>
<P>LONDON, Printed for J. SCOTT, in Pater-no&s;ter-Row. MDCCLVII.</P>
